  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to have an obvious and simple way how to install or uninstall application\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\n### Installation notes:\r\n- build is stored in `.zip` format (expected in `.dmg` for Mac OSx), so you need special software to unzip it.\r\n- when you launch StatusIm for the first time, it produces a lot of files in the same folder \r\n- `StatusIm` app is not registered as separate app, so it cannot be found in Launchpad\r\n- `StatusIm` file cannot be found using Spotlight Search, so you should manually open unzipped folder every time you want launch application\r\n### Uninstallation notes:\r\n- to remove `StatusIm` from your laptop you can use separate app (i.e. `CleanMyMac`) or manually stop application and remove all related files.\r\n\r\nAll this make user do a lot of additional actions just for install/uninstall app, what is quite inconvenient.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\n- [x] installation package - in `.dmg` format\r\n- [x] service files are stored in ~/Library/Application Support\r\n- [ ]  `StatusIm` is separate app, can be found in Applications, Launchpad and through Spotlight Search\r\n- [x]  `StatusIm` can be deleted from Applications folder\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: ...\r\n* Operating System: Mac OSx High Sierre\r\n\r\n\r\n",
